      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "Mining empty blocks can happen, although the occurence of it seems to be dropping. If I'm not mistaken it usually occurs when mining pools begin preemptively mining the next block if they think they are already late on the current one.\r\n\r\nI think if the devs don't find the time between the blocks too alarming then Bitcoin Stack Exchange is a good place to discuss this: https://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/",
